  "evidence_excerpts": [
    {
      "text": "Indexed\n45\n10\n\nI want to say something about the Logos -the principle of world reason- + St. Sophia, divine wisdom (they are combined in Christ). This is the instrument of God by which the universe runs; it is the Nous of the Greeks. To me, this was always God's essence (cf Heidegger: \"Noein + einai combined\" - the ultimate ideal). What this as ultimate principle leads to is Roman + Greek serenity + stoicism. For me, joy is to be preferred, even though it allows error, pain, evil + futility. Nie",
